# Code Quality Rules

## Error Handling
- ALL async functions MUST handle errors explicitly
- NEVER ignore rejected promises
- NEVER use empty catch blocks

## Async Safety
- Avoid race conditions in async flows
- Always cancel side effects in coroutines
- Do not update state after activity destroyed

## Data Integrity
- NEVER trust external data (API, user input)
- ALWAYS validate response shape
- Use explicit null checks

## Performance
- Avoid unnecessary re-compositions
- Use remember/derivedStateOf ONLY when needed
- Do not introduce O(n²) logic without justification

## Code Structure
- Functions MUST have single responsibility
- Avoid deeply nested logic (>3 levels)
- Extract reusable logic into utilities

## Review Focus Override
When reviewing:
- PRIORITIZE: bugs, async issues, data safety
- IGNORE: formatting, stylistic preferences